## Problem
Mode A must call a **stable CLI** rather than freestyling `herdr agent start` shell. Need user-facing commands that resolve CLIs (B055), ensure session + start (B056), and optionally inject a kickoff prompt.

## Scope (I005 / B057)
CLI surface + wiring to library. Skill copy is B058.

## Suggested CLI
```text
hark session list [--json]
hark session ensure <name> [--json]

hark agent-start <agent> [--session ID] [--cwd PATH] [--name LABEL]
                 [--split right|down] [--no-focus]
                 [--prompt TEXT] [--argv ...]   # ad-hoc after --
```

- `<agent>`: catalog key or alias (`claude`, `cc`, `codex`, …) **or** ad-hoc binary when using `--argv` / `--` form
- `--prompt`: after successful start, `send_text` kickoff + Enter; speak-friendly JSON includes target
- Default session: configured default / `local` / active herdr session (document choice)
- Exit codes follow existing hark convention (Herdr → 3)

## Acceptance
- [ ] CLI registered in `cli.py` with help text
- [ ] Resolves known agents via B055; supports ad-hoc argv
- [ ] Optional kickoff prompt uses safe send_text submit path
- [ ] `--json` output includes session_id, pane_id, argv used, source (alias/canonical)
- [ ] Smoke test or unit test of argparse + mocked client